+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Thread Classification
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+Authoritative triage is recorded in `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`.
+
+## Changes Applied
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`: normalized the incoming approval state before building the preview payload so router callers no longer leak `manual_review` into preview responses.
+- `src/policy/preview.py`: preserved `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in both live and fallback preview payloads while keeping the existing fallback `status`.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`: extended the writable preview suite with a regression covering disabled preview plus `manual_review` normalization, and tightened the fallback assertions to require the human-review fields.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`: corrected the fallback example payload and clarified that fallback responses preserve the normalized approval state.
+
+## Verification
+
+- `python -m unittest tests.test_preview`
+- `python -m unittest tests.test_approval_router`
+
+Both test commands passed on this branch.
