@@ -0,0 +1,14 @@
+`T-214-01`:
+Updated the preview fallback payload so it now preserves `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` even when `preview_enabled=False`. The router also normalizes `manual_review` to `human_review_required` before the payload is built, so the fallback path now matches the live-preview path.
+
+`T-214-02`:
+Handled as a duplicate of `T-214-01`. The same fallback fix covers this reopened payload issue as well.
+
+`T-214-03`:
+Not applied. This comment points at an outdated router hunk and suggests reviving legacy preview behavior on the current branch. The remediation keeps the current path and fixes normalization instead; no legacy branch or hint was reintroduced.
+
+`T-214-04`:
+Added a regression test covering `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"` through `build_policy_preview(...)`. The assertion now verifies the normalized fallback payload includes `approval_state="human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review=True`.
+
+`T-214-05`:
+Updated the approval policy docs so the fallback example now shows `approval_state: "human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review: true`.
